  "prompt": "Which are the top ninja dragon games?",
  "response": "Ninja dragon games combine the thrill of ninja combat with the mystique of dragons, creating unique and exciting gameplay experiences. Here are some of the top ninja dragon games across various platforms:\n\n---\n\n### **Mobile Games**\n1. **Ninja Arashi**  \n   - A fast-paced action platformer where you play as a ninja seeking revenge. While dragons aren't the main focus, the ninja combat and fantasy elements make it a great choice.  \n   - Available on Android and iOS.\n\n2. **Dragon City**  \n   - While not strictly a ninja game, Dragon City allows you to collect and breed dragons, including ninja-themed dragons, and build your own dragon empire.  \n   - Available on Android, iOS, and Facebook.\n\n3. **Ninja Village**  \n   A strategy game where you build your village, train ninjas, and command dragons in battle. The combination of ninjas and dragons makes it a unique experience.  \n   - Available on Android and iOS.\n\n---\n\n### **PC and Console Games**\n4. **Shadow of the Ninja** (Retro)  \n   - A classic action platformer on the NES where players control ninjas battling through a futuristic world. While dragons aren't prominent, the ninja theme is strong.  \n   - Available on retro consoles or emulators.\n\n5. **Ninja Gaiden Series**  \n   - This iconic series features intense ninja combat and occasionally incorporates mythical creatures like dragons into its storyline.  \n   - Available on Xbox, PlayStation, and PC.\n\n6. **Dragon Ninja** (Bad Dudes)  \n   - A retro arcade game where players fight as ninjas to save the president from a dragon. It\u2019s a classic for fans of ninjas and dragons.  \n   - Available on retro arcade systems.\n\n---\n\n### **Browser Games**\n7. **Ninja vs Dragon**  \n   - A browser-based game where you play as a ninja fighting dragons in a side-scrolling action adventure. Simple but fun.  \n\n8. **Dragon\u2019s Quest RPG**  \n   - A browser RPG where ninjas and dragons coexist in a fantasy world. The game focuses on strategy and combat.\n\n---\n\n### **Upcoming Games**\n9. **Ninja Dragon: Shadow of Fate** (Rumored)  \n   - A rumored upcoming game that promises to combine ninja stealth mechanics with dragon companions in an open-world setting. Keep an eye out for updates!\n\n---\n\nIf you\u2019re looking for a specific type of gameplay (e.g., action, strategy, or RPG), let me know so I can tailor recommendations further!",
